176static int load_x509(const char *file, char **filenameptr,
177 vchar_t **certptr)
178{
179 char path[PATH_MAX];
180
181 getpathname(path, sizeof(path), LC_PATHTYPE_CERT, file);
182 *certptr = eay_get_x509cert(path);
183 if (*certptr == NULL)
184 return -1;
185
186 *filenameptr = racoon_strdup(file);
187 STRDUP_FATAL(*filenameptr);
188
189 return 0;
190}
191
192static int process_rmconf(void)
193{
194
195 /* check a exchange mode */
196 if (cur_rmconf->etypes == NULL) {
197 yyerror("no exchange mode specified.\n");
198 return -1;
199 }
200
201 if (cur_rmconf->idvtype == IDTYPE_UNDEFINED)
202 cur_rmconf->idvtype = IDTYPE_ADDRESS;
203
204 if (cur_rmconf->idvtype == IDTYPE_ASN1DN) {
205 if (cur_rmconf->mycertfile) {
206 if (cur_rmconf->idv)
207 yywarn("Both CERT and ASN1 ID "
208 "are set. Hope this is OK.\n");
209 /* TODO: Preparse the DN here */
210 } else if (cur_rmconf->idv) {
211 /* OK, using asn1dn without X.509. */
212 } else {
213 yyerror("ASN1 ID not specified "
214 "and no CERT defined!\n");
215 return -1;
216 }
217 }
218
219 if (duprmconf_finish(cur_rmconf))
220 return -1;
221
222 if (set_isakmp_proposal(cur_rmconf) != 0)
223 return -1;
224
225 /* DH group settting if aggressive mode is there. */
226 if (check_etypeok(cur_rmconf, (void*) ISAKMP_ETYPE_AGG)) {
227 struct isakmpsa *p;
228 int b = 0;
229
230 /* DH group */
231 for (p = cur_rmconf->proposal; p; p = p->next) {
232 if (b == 0 || (b && b == p->dh_group)) {
233 b = p->dh_group;
234 continue;
235 }
236 yyerror("DH group must be equal "
237 "in all proposals "
238 "when aggressive mode is "
239 "used.\n");
240 return -1;
241 }
242 cur_rmconf->dh_group = b;
243
244 if (cur_rmconf->dh_group == 0) {
245 yyerror("DH group must be set in the proposal.\n");
246 return -1;
247 }
248
249 /* DH group settting if PFS is required. */
250 if (oakley_setdhgroup(cur_rmconf->dh_group,
251 &cur_rmconf->dhgrp) < 0) {
252 yyerror("failed to set DH value.\n");
253 return -1;
254 }
255 }
256
257 insrmconf(cur_rmconf);
258 cur_rmconf = NULL;
259
260 return 0;
261}

270/* macros for aborting the parsing with freeing up allocated memory */
271#define ABORT_CLEANUP {delrmconf(cur_rmconf); delsainfo(cur_sainfo); YYABORT;}
272#define ABORT() ABORT_CLEANUP
273
274#define ABORT_AND_VFREE(val0) {\
275 vfree(val0); val0 = NULL;\
276 ABORT_CLEANUP}
277
278#define ABORT_AND_RACOON_FREE(val0) {\
279 racoon_free(val0); val0 = NULL;\
280 ABORT_CLEANUP}
281

283 vfree(val0); val0 = NULL;\
284 vfree(val1); val1 = NULL;\
285 ABORT_CLEANUP}

1779static struct secprotospec *
1780newspspec()
1781{
1782 struct secprotospec *new;
1783
1784 new = racoon_calloc(1, sizeof(*new));
1785 if (new == NULL) {
1786 yyerror("failed to allocate spproto");
1787 return NULL;
1788 }
1789
1790 new->encklen = 0; /*XXX*/
1791
1792 /*
1793 * Default to "uknown" vendor -- we will override this
1794 * as necessary. When we send a Vendor ID payload, an
1795 * "unknown" will be translated to a KAME/racoon ID.
1796 */
1797 new->vendorid = VENDORID_UNKNOWN;
1798
1799 return new;
1800}

1808 struct secprotospec *spspec;

1816static struct secprotospec *
1817dupspspec(struct secprotospec *spspec)
1818{
1819 struct secprotospec *new;
1820
1821 new = newspspec();
1822 if (new == NULL) {
1823 plog(LLV_ERROR, LOCATION, NULL,
1824 "dupspspec: malloc failed\n");
1825 return NULL;
1826 }
1827 memcpy(new, spspec, sizeof(*new));
1828
1829 if (spspec->gssid) {
1830 new->gssid = racoon_strdup(spspec->gssid);
1831 STRDUP_FATAL(new->gssid);
1832 }
1833 if (spspec->remote) {
1834 new->remote = racoon_malloc(sizeof(*new->remote));
1835 if (new->remote == NULL) {
1836 plog(LLV_ERROR, LOCATION, NULL,
1837 "dupspspec: malloc failed (remote)\n");
1838 return NULL;
1839 }
1840 memcpy(new->remote, spspec->remote, sizeof(*new->remote));
1841 }
1842
1843 return new;
1844}

1846/*
1847 * copy the whole list
1848 */
1849void
1850dupspspec_list(dst, src)
1851 struct remoteconf *dst, *src;
1852{
1853 struct secprotospec *p, *new, *last;
1854
1855 for(p = src->spspec, last = NULL; p; p = p->next, last = new) {
1856 new = dupspspec(p);
1857 if (new == NULL)
1858 exit(1);
1859
1860 new->prev = last;
1861 new->next = NULL; /* not necessary but clean */
1862
1863 if (last)
1864 last->next = new;
1865 else /* first element */
1866 dst->spspec = new;
1867
1868 }
1869}

1871/*
1872 * delete the whole list
1873 */
1874void
1875flushspspec(rmconf)
1876 struct remoteconf *rmconf;
1877{
1878 struct secprotospec *p;
1879
1880 while(rmconf->spspec != NULL) {
1881 p = rmconf->spspec;
1882 rmconf->spspec = p->next;
1883 if (p->next != NULL)
1884 p->next->prev = NULL; /* not necessary but clean */
1885
1886 if (p->gssid)
1887 racoon_free(p->gssid);
1888 if (p->remote)
1889 racoon_free(p->remote);
1890 racoon_free(p);
1891 }
1892 rmconf->spspec = NULL;
1893}

1895/* set final acceptable proposal */
1896static int
1897set_isakmp_proposal(rmconf)
1898 struct remoteconf *rmconf;
1899{
1900 struct secprotospec *s;
1901 int prop_no = 1;
1902 int trns_no = 1;
1903 int32_t types[MAXALGCLASS];
1904
1905 /* mandatory check */
1906 if (rmconf->spspec == NULL) {
1907 yyerror("no remote specification found: %s.\n",
1908 saddr2str(rmconf->remote));
1909 return -1;
1910 }
1911 for (s = rmconf->spspec; s != NULL; s = s->next) {
1912 /* XXX need more to check */
1913 if (s->algclass[algclass_isakmp_enc] == 0) {
1914 yyerror("encryption algorithm required.");
1915 return -1;
1916 }
1917 if (s->algclass[algclass_isakmp_hash] == 0) {
1918 yyerror("hash algorithm required.");
1919 return -1;
1920 }
1921 if (s->algclass[algclass_isakmp_dh] == 0) {
1922 yyerror("DH group required.");
1923 return -1;
1924 }
1925 if (s->algclass[algclass_isakmp_ameth] == 0) {
1926 yyerror("authentication method required.");
1927 return -1;
1928 }
1929 }
1930
1931 /* skip to last part */
1932 for (s = rmconf->spspec; s->next != NULL; s = s->next)
1933 ;
1934
1935 while (s != NULL) {
1936 plog(LLV_DEBUG2, LOCATION, NULL,
1937 "lifetime = %ld\n", (long)
1938 (s->lifetime ? s->lifetime : rmconf->lifetime));
1939 plog(LLV_DEBUG2, LOCATION, NULL,
1940 "lifebyte = %d\n",
1941 s->lifebyte ? s->lifebyte : rmconf->lifebyte);
1942 plog(LLV_DEBUG2, LOCATION, NULL,
1943 "encklen=%d\n", s->encklen);
1944
1945 memset(types, 0, ARRAYLEN(types));
1946 types[algclass_isakmp_enc] = s->algclass[algclass_isakmp_enc];
1947 types[algclass_isakmp_hash] = s->algclass[algclass_isakmp_hash];
1948 types[algclass_isakmp_dh] = s->algclass[algclass_isakmp_dh];
1949 types[algclass_isakmp_ameth] =
1950 s->algclass[algclass_isakmp_ameth];
1951
1952 /* expanding spspec */
1953 clean_tmpalgtype();
1954 trns_no = expand_isakmpspec(prop_no, trns_no, types,
1955 algclass_isakmp_enc, algclass_isakmp_ameth + 1,
1956 s->lifetime ? s->lifetime : rmconf->lifetime,
1957 s->lifebyte ? s->lifebyte : rmconf->lifebyte,
1958 s->encklen, s->vendorid, s->gssid,
1959 rmconf);
1960 if (trns_no == -1) {
1961 plog(LLV_ERROR, LOCATION, NULL,
1962 "failed to expand isakmp proposal.\n");
1963 return -1;
1964 }
1965
1966 s = s->prev;
1967 }
1968
1969 if (rmconf->proposal == NULL) {
1970 plog(LLV_ERROR, LOCATION, NULL,
1971 "no proposal found.\n");
1972 return -1;
1973 }

2096int
2097cfparse()
2098{
2099 int error;
2100
2101 yyerrorcount = 0;
2102 yycf_init_buffer();
2103
2104 if (yycf_switch_buffer(lcconf->racoon_conf) != 0) {
2105 plog(LLV_ERROR, LOCATION, NULL,
2106 "could not read configuration file \"%s\"\n",
2107 lcconf->racoon_conf);
2108 return -1;
2109 }
2110
2111 error = yyparse();
2112 if (error != 0) {
2113 if (yyerrorcount) {
2114 plog(LLV_ERROR, LOCATION, NULL,
2115 "fatal parse failure (%d errors)\n",
2116 yyerrorcount);
2117 } else {
2118 plog(LLV_ERROR, LOCATION, NULL,
2119 "fatal parse failure.\n");
2120 }
2121 return -1;
2122 }
2123
2124 if (error == 0 && yyerrorcount) {
2125 plog(LLV_ERROR, LOCATION, NULL,
2126 "parse error is nothing, but yyerrorcount is %d.\n",
2127 yyerrorcount);
2128 exit(1);
2129 }
2130
2131 yycf_clean_buffer();
2132
2133 plog(LLV_DEBUG2, LOCATION, NULL, "parse successed.\n");
2134
2135 return 0;

2353int
2354YYPARSE_DECL()
2355{
2356 int yym, yyn, yystate, yyresult;
2357#if YYBTYACC
2358 int yynewerrflag;
2359 YYParseState *yyerrctx = NULL;
2360#endif /* YYBTYACC */
2361#if defined(YYLTYPE) || defined(YYLTYPE_IS_DECLARED)
2362 YYLTYPE yyerror_loc_range[3]; /* position of error start/end (0 unused) */
2363#endif
2364#if YYDEBUG
2365 const char *yys;
2366
2367 if ((yys = getenv("YYDEBUG")) != 0)
2368 {
2369 yyn = *yys;
2370 if (yyn >= '0' && yyn <= '9')
2371 yydebug = yyn - '0';
2372 }
2373 if (yydebug)
2374 fprintf(stderr, "%sdebug[<# of symbols on state stack>]\n", YYPREFIX);
2375#endif
2376#if defined(YYLTYPE) || defined(YYLTYPE_IS_DECLARED)
2377 memset(yyerror_loc_range, 0, sizeof(yyerror_loc_range));
2378#endif
2379
2380#if YYBTYACC
2381 yyps = yyNewState(0); if (yyps == 0) goto yyenomem;
2382 yyps->save = 0;
2383#endif /* YYBTYACC */
2384 yym = 0;
2385 yyn = 0;
2386 yynerrs = 0;
2387 yyerrflag = 0;
2388 yychar = YYEMPTY;
2389 yystate = 0;
2390
2391#if YYPURE
2392 memset(&yystack, 0, sizeof(yystack));
2393#endif
2394
2395 if (yystack.s_base == NULL && yygrowstack(&yystack) == YYENOMEM) goto yyoverflow;
2396 yystack.s_mark = yystack.s_base;
2397 yystack.l_mark = yystack.l_base;
2398#if defined(YYLTYPE) || defined(YYLTYPE_IS_DECLARED)
2399 yystack.p_mark = yystack.p_base;
2400#endif
2401 yystate = 0;
2402 *yystack.s_mark = 0;
2403
2404yyloop:
2405 if ((yyn = yydefred[yystate]) != 0) goto yyreduce;
2406 if (yychar < 0)
2407 {
2408#if YYBTYACC
2409 do {
2410 if (yylvp < yylve)
2411 {
2412 /* we're currently re-reading tokens */
2413 yylval = *yylvp++;
2414#if defined(YYLTYPE) || defined(YYLTYPE_IS_DECLARED)
2415 yylloc = *yylpp++;
2416#endif
2417 yychar = *yylexp++;
2418 break;
2419 }
2420 if (yyps->save)
2421 {
2422 /* in trial mode; save scanner results for future parse attempts */
2423 if (yylvp == yylvlim)
2424 { /* Enlarge lexical value queue */
2425 size_t p = (size_t) (yylvp - yylvals);
2426 size_t s = (size_t) (yylvlim - yylvals);
2427
2428 s += YYLVQUEUEGROWTH;
2429 if ((yylexemes = (YYINT *)realloc(yylexemes, s * sizeof(YYINT))) == NULL) goto yyenomem;
2430 if ((yylvals = (YYSTYPE *)realloc(yylvals, s * sizeof(YYSTYPE))) == NULL) goto yyenomem;
2431#if defined(YYLTYPE) || defined(YYLTYPE_IS_DECLARED)
2432 if ((yylpsns = (YYLTYPE *)realloc(yylpsns, s * sizeof(YYLTYPE))) == NULL) goto yyenomem;
2433#endif
2434 yylvp = yylve = yylvals + p;
2435 yylvlim = yylvals + s;
2436#if defined(YYLTYPE) || defined(YYLTYPE_IS_DECLARED)
2437 yylpp = yylpe = yylpsns + p;
2438 yylplim = yylpsns + s;
2439#endif
2440 yylexp = yylexemes + p;
2441 }
2442 *yylexp = (YYINT) YYLEX;
2443 *yylvp++ = yylval;
2444 yylve++;
2445#if defined(YYLTYPE) || defined(YYLTYPE_IS_DECLARED)
2446 *yylpp++ = yylloc;
2447 yylpe++;
2448#endif
2449 yychar = *yylexp++;
2450 break;
2451 }
2452 /* normal operation, no conflict encountered */
2453#endif /* YYBTYACC */
2454 yychar = YYLEX;
2455#if YYBTYACC
2456 } while (0);
2457#endif /* YYBTYACC */
2458 if (yychar < 0) yychar = YYEOF;
2459#if YYDEBUG
2460 if (yydebug)
2461 {
2462 if ((yys = yyname[YYTRANSLATE(yychar)]) == NULL) yys = yyname[YYUNDFTOKEN];

5252 }
5253 if (yyps->save)
5254 {
5255 /* in trial mode; save scanner results for future parse attempts */
5256 if (yylvp == yylvlim)
5257 { /* Enlarge lexical value queue */
5258 size_t p = (size_t) (yylvp - yylvals);
5259 size_t s = (size_t) (yylvlim - yylvals);
5260
5261 s += YYLVQUEUEGROWTH;
5262 if ((yylexemes = (YYINT *)realloc(yylexemes, s * sizeof(YYINT))) == NULL)
5263 goto yyenomem;
5264 if ((yylvals = (YYSTYPE *)realloc(yylvals, s * sizeof(YYSTYPE))) == NULL)
5265 goto yyenomem;
5266#if defined(YYLTYPE) || defined(YYLTYPE_IS_DECLARED)
5267 if ((yylpsns = (YYLTYPE *)realloc(yylpsns, s * sizeof(YYLTYPE))) == NULL)
5268 goto yyenomem;
5269#endif
5270 yylvp = yylve = yylvals + p;
5271 yylvlim = yylvals + s;
5272#if defined(YYLTYPE) || defined(YYLTYPE_IS_DECLARED)
5273 yylpp = yylpe = yylpsns + p;
5274 yylplim = yylpsns + s;
5275#endif
5276 yylexp = yylexemes + p;
5277 }
5278 *yylexp = (YYINT) YYLEX;
5279 *yylvp++ = yylval;
5280 yylve++;
5281#if defined(YYLTYPE) || defined(YYLTYPE_IS_DECLARED)
5282 *yylpp++ = yylloc;
5283 yylpe++;
5284#endif
5285 yychar = *yylexp++;
5286 break;
5287 }
5288 /* normal operation, no conflict encountered */
5289#endif /* YYBTYACC */
5290 yychar = YYLEX;
5291#if YYBTYACC
5292 } while (0);
5293#endif /* YYBTYACC */
5294 if (yychar < 0) yychar = YYEOF;
5295#if YYDEBUG
5296 if (yydebug)
5297 {
5298 if ((yys = yyname[YYTRANSLATE(yychar)]) == NULL) yys = yyname[YYUNDFTOKEN];
5299 fprintf(stderr, "%s[%d]: state %d, reading token %d (%s)\n",
5300 YYDEBUGSTR, yydepth, YYFINAL, yychar, yys);
5301 }
5302#endif
5303 }
5304 if (yychar == YYEOF) goto yyaccept;
5305 goto yyloop;
5306 }
5307 if (((yyn = yygindex[yym]) != 0) && (yyn += yystate) >= 0 &&
5308 yyn <= YYTABLESIZE && yycheck[yyn] == (YYINT) yystate)
5309 yystate = yytable[yyn];
5310 else
5311 yystate = yydgoto[yym];
5312#if YYDEBUG
5313 if (yydebug)
5314 {
5315 fprintf(stderr, "%s[%d]: after reduction, ", YYDEBUGSTR, yydepth);
5316#ifdef YYSTYPE_TOSTRING
5317#if YYBTYACC
5318 if (!yytrial)
5319#endif /* YYBTYACC */
5320 fprintf(stderr, "result is <%s>, ", YYSTYPE_TOSTRING(yystos[yystate], yyval));
5321#endif
5322 fprintf(stderr, "shifting from state %d to state %d\n", *yystack.s_mark, yystate);
5323 }
5324#endif
5325 if (yystack.s_mark >= yystack.s_last && yygrowstack(&yystack) == YYENOMEM) goto yyoverflow;
5326 *++yystack.s_mark = (YYINT) yystate;
5327 *++yystack.l_mark = yyval;
5328#if defined(YYLTYPE) || defined(YYLTYPE_IS_DECLARED)
5329 *++yystack.p_mark = yyloc;
5330#endif
5331 goto yyloop;
5332#if YYBTYACC
5333
5334 /* Reduction declares that this path is valid. Set yypath and do a full parse */
5335yyvalid:
5336 if (yypath) YYABORT;
5337 while (yyps->save)
5338 {
5339 YYParseState *save = yyps->save;
5340 yyps->save = save->save;
5341 save->save = yypath;
5342 yypath = save;
5343 }
5344#if YYDEBUG
5345 if (yydebug)
5346 fprintf(stderr, "%s[%d]: state %d, CONFLICT trial successful, backtracking to state %d, %d tokens\n",
5347 YYDEBUGSTR, yydepth, yystate, yypath->state, (int)(yylvp - yylvals - yypath->lexeme));
5348#endif
5349 if (yyerrctx)
5350 {
5351 yyFreeState(yyerrctx);
5352 yyerrctx = NULL;
5353 }
5354 yylvp = yylvals + yypath->lexeme;
5355#if defined(YYLTYPE) || defined(YYLTYPE_IS_DECLARED)
5356 yylpp = yylpsns + yypath->lexeme;
5357#endif
5358 yylexp = yylexemes + yypath->lexeme;
5359 yychar = YYEMPTY;
5360 yystack.s_mark = yystack.s_base + (yypath->yystack.s_mark - yypath->yystack.s_base);
5361 memcpy (yystack.s_base, yypath->yystack.s_base, (size_t) (yystack.s_mark - yystack.s_base + 1) * sizeof(YYINT));
5362 yystack.l_mark = yystack.l_base + (yypath->yystack.l_mark - yypath->yystack.l_base);
5363 memcpy (yystack.l_base, yypath->yystack.l_base, (size_t) (yystack.l_mark - yystack.l_base + 1) * sizeof(YYSTYPE));
5364#if defined(YYLTYPE) || defined(YYLTYPE_IS_DECLARED)
5365 yystack.p_mark = yystack.p_base + (yypath->yystack.p_mark - yypath->yystack.p_base);
5366 memcpy (yystack.p_base, yypath->yystack.p_base, (size_t) (yystack.p_mark - yystack.p_base + 1) * sizeof(YYLTYPE));
5367#endif
5368 yystate = yypath->state;
5369 goto yyloop;
5370#endif /* YYBTYACC */
5371
5372yyoverflow:
5373 YYERROR_CALL("yacc stack overflow");
5374#if YYBTYACC
5375 goto yyabort_nomem;
5376yyenomem:
5377 YYERROR_CALL("memory exhausted");
5378yyabort_nomem:
5379#endif /* YYBTYACC */
5380 yyresult = 2;
5381 goto yyreturn;
5382
5383yyabort:
5384 yyresult = 1;
5385 goto yyreturn;
5386
5387yyaccept:
5388#if YYBTYACC
5389 if (yyps->save) goto yyvalid;
5390#endif /* YYBTYACC */
5391 yyresult = 0;
5392
5393yyreturn:
5394#if defined(YYDESTRUCT_CALL)
5395 if (yychar != YYEOF && yychar != YYEMPTY)
5396#if defined(YYLTYPE) || defined(YYLTYPE_IS_DECLARED)
5397 YYDESTRUCT_CALL("cleanup: discarding token", yychar, &yylval, &yylloc);
5398#else
5399 YYDESTRUCT_CALL("cleanup: discarding token", yychar, &yylval);
5400#endif /* defined(YYLTYPE) || defined(YYLTYPE_IS_DECLARED) */
5401
5402 {
5403 YYSTYPE *pv;
5404#if defined(YYLTYPE) || defined(YYLTYPE_IS_DECLARED)
5405 YYLTYPE *pp;
5406
5407 for (pv = yystack.l_base, pp = yystack.p_base; pv <= yystack.l_mark; ++pv, ++pp)
5408 YYDESTRUCT_CALL("cleanup: discarding state",
5409 yystos[*(yystack.s_base + (pv - yystack.l_base))], pv, pp);
5410#else
5411 for (pv = yystack.l_base; pv <= yystack.l_mark; ++pv)
5412 YYDESTRUCT_CALL("cleanup: discarding state",
5413 yystos[*(yystack.s_base + (pv - yystack.l_base))], pv);
5414#endif /* defined(YYLTYPE) || defined(YYLTYPE_IS_DECLARED) */
5415 }
5416#endif /* defined(YYDESTRUCT_CALL) */
5417
5418#if YYBTYACC
5419 if (yyerrctx)
5420 {
5421 yyFreeState(yyerrctx);
5422 yyerrctx = NULL;
5423 }
5424 while (yyps)
5425 {
5426 YYParseState *save = yyps;
5427 yyps = save->save;
5428 save->save = NULL;
5429 yyFreeState(save);
5430 }
5431 while (yypath)
5432 {
5433 YYParseState *save = yypath;
5434 yypath = save->save;
5435 save->save = NULL;
5436 yyFreeState(save);
5437 }
5438#endif /* YYBTYACC */
5439 yyfreestack(&yystack);
5440 return (yyresult);
5441}
